<b>Ralston Hill</b> was a stage actor, born <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../734/2734.xml">
April 24</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../939/34939.xml">
1927</link>, died <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../568/22568.xml">
October 19</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../636/34636.xml">
1996</link>, and had many roles on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../252/725252.xml">
Broadway</link>, most notably Congressional Secretary Charles Thomson in the play and movie <movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../033/11600033.xml">
1776</link></movie>
. His only film credit is that same role in the musical <musical wordnetid="107019172" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../607/161607.xml">
1776</link></musical>
. 


